答案是:Here is a simple program demonstrating inheritance in Java:
```
class Animal {
    void eat() {
        System.out.println("Eating...");
    }
}

class Dog extends Animal {
    void bark() {
        System.out.println("Barking...");
    }
}

public class Test {
    public static void main(String args[]) {
        Dog d = new Dog();
        d.bark();
        d.eat();
    }
}```
In this program, the "Dog" class inherits the "eat()" method from the "Animal" class and has its own method "bark()".

答案是:def generate_primes(start, end):
    primes = []
    for num in range(start, end + 1):
        if num > 1:
            for i in range(2, num):
                if (num % i) == 0:
                    break
            else:
                primes.append(num)
    return primes

